# Slotomania Monetization-Art (Monday + CRM3)

You create and fill Monday.com art brief items on the **Monetization-Art** board by duplicating templates, moving to the correct group, setting columns, and writing **subitem updates** (briefs). Use **CRM3** on the studio share for real references and previews.

## Authentication & tools

- **Monday API**: `MONDAY_API_TOKEN` in `.cursor/monday.env` (gitignored). Never commit tokens.
- Prefer GraphQL v2 (`https://api.monday.com/v2`) via `scripts/monday_client.py` when MCP is blocked.
- **CRM3**: `smb://dfs-il/studios/Slotomania/CRM3` (Mac: often `/Volumes/CRM3`). Brief paths: `Q:\Slotomania\CRM3\...`

## Board conventions (verify on account)

- Board ID: **18112190666** (Monetization-Art)
- Default group example: `group_mm3fs1q5` (“2026-11-11 - test”) — user may specify another
- Columns:
  - `date4` — promo date `{"date": "YYYY-MM-DD"}`
  - `text_mkwe4jsr` — art folder link (`Q:\Slotomania\CRM3\...`)
  - `color_mky3swe2` — Product (labels must match board exactly; many Coin Sale items leave Product empty)
  - `date_mkwj8wwp` — Brief Due Date
  - `date_mkwep612` — Art Due Date
  - `color_mkws3h8e` — Priority: Critical ⚠️️ / High / Medium / Low
  - `status` — Status Creative; board label `done` means Completed
- Item name via `name` in `change_multiple_column_values`

## Mandatory workflow (every new promo)

1. Find template on board (Coins Sale, Dynamic JP, Buy All, Daily Deal, RYD, Rolling Offer, PYP, MES, etc.)
2. `duplicate_item(board_id, item_id)` — do not invent `create_item` + duplicate id
3. `change_multiple_column_values` — name, promo date, art path; Product only if label exists
4. `move_item_to_group` — user’s group (duplicate often lands in Templates)
5. `create_update` on parent — theme, mechanics, art folder, CRM3 note
6. `create_update` on **every subitem** — briefs live in updates, not description (duplication does not copy subitem updates)
7. Wait 2–3s after duplicate if subitems empty, then re-query subitems before posting briefs

## References

- **Reference Link** = full file path: `Q:\Slotomania\CRM3\...\filename.png` (not folder-only)
- **Reference** = embedded preview: upload from CRM3 via `add_file_to_update` → `/v2/file`, then optional `edit_update` with `https://playtika.monday.com/protected_static/7996532/resources/{asset_id}/{filename}`
- Reference art must match the subitem asset type: Inapp→Inapp, Banner→Banner, Widget→Widget, etc. Never reuse one generic preview across unlike assets.
- If no matching historical asset exists, say so explicitly and leave the preview empty; never attach a misleading reference.
- For art briefs use the promo date the user wants (not “exclude incomplete today” analytics rules)

## Brief standards

- HTML tables in updates when template expects rows (Background, Main Messages, Art guidelines, Reference, Reference Link, CTA, etc.)
- Coin Sale: include PU / IC / DPU / NPU coin % tiers unless user overrides
- State theme + mechanic clearly; art folder under `Features\...` or `Holidays & Events\{Event}\{year}\Coin_Sale`
- Every subitem must state the exact Creative action for that asset. Never use a generic “prepare/adapt” instruction.
- End every parent brief with **Creative Request**: exact deliverables, or “No creative action — Completed.”
- **Reuse**: name the exact source promo/date and asset. Parent Status Creative=`done`; each no-action subitem Copy Status=`Done` and Art Status=`Done`.
- Due dates: Brief Due = promo date − 7 calendar days minimum; Art Due = promo date − 2 calendar days minimum. If either lands Friday/Saturday, move it backward to Thursday.
- Priority default: Critical for business-critical launch with no fallback; High for new promo/theme or broad anchor package; Medium for prize/mission changes; Low for Reuse, backup, or no-action work. Override only with explicit business context.
- If CRM3 not mounted: set paths and note “upload previews when CRM3 available”

## User request handling

Ask only if missing: theme, promo date, group, SKUs/mechanics.

Return: Monday pulse URL, item name, date, art path, subitems briefed.

## GraphQL

```graphql
mutation { duplicate_item(board_id: ID!, item_id: ID!) { id } }
mutation { change_multiple_column_values(board_id: ID!, item_id: ID!, column_values: JSON!) { id } }
mutation { move_item_to_group(item_id: ID!, group_id: String!) { id } }
mutation { create_update(item_id: ID!, body: String!) { id } }
mutation { edit_update(id: ID!, body: String!) { id } }
```

Per-promo scripts: `scripts/add_*_monday.py` sourcing `.cursor/monday.env`.
